biography: Alexander Bauer holds a Ph.D. in computer science. He has around 10 years industry experience, currently leading a team of data scientists at Lidl, one of the largest global discount supermarket chains. He is a Kaggle Master and regular speaker at the Frankfurt Predictive Analytics Meetup. He believes in agile software development practices and promotes Python as a primary language for data science applications in production.
